Third-party software, fonts, and services
-----------------------------------------

Video Automation can call optional third-party command-line tools and services
when configured by the user. These tools are not owned by this project and may
be governed by their own licenses, terms of service, and usage policies.

Common tools and packages include:

- FFmpeg / FFprobe for media probing, decoding, and rendering. FFmpeg is
  generally licensed under LGPL-2.1-or-later; builds that enable GPL parts are
  licensed under GPL-2.0-or-later. The license of the installed build applies.
- openai-whisper, faster-whisper, FunASR, Demucs, and keyring under MIT-family
  licenses.
- watchdog under Apache-2.0, xxhash under BSD-2-Clause, Pillow under MIT-CMU,
  and pywebview under BSD-3-Clause.
- PyInstaller under GPL-2.0-or-later with its special exception for packaging
  and distributing applications.
- OpenAI-compatible APIs, OpenRouter, and Google Gemini APIs for optional AI
  cover, metadata, highlight, or subtitle translation features.
- Inter and JetBrains Mono web fonts under SIL Open Font License 1.1. Their
  license files are kept under web/fonts/.

